&lt;p&gt;We are holding an assessment day for dynamic and motivated Band 5 Nurses to join our Emergency department at the Royal London Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the day:&lt;br /&gt;- You can meet the team and discuss career opportunities&lt;br /&gt;- You will undertake assessments and interviews on the same day&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer a structured orientation programme and on-going supportive mentorship to ensure you quickly progress and meet the standards to join the specialist Emergency Nurse Development programme which will offer the potential for practice experience in other emergency care provision areas such as Minor Injuries, and Paediatric ED.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have over six months&#39; acute post registration experience with the skills and abilities to deliver high standards of care and have the resilience to meet the challenges of our busy and stimulating work environment. You should be self-motivated, an excellent communicator and have proven organisational / clinical skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With a diverse range of career options to match the enormous range of services we provide, we can help you develop your career and grow with Barts Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ED Nursing team on rlhed.nurserecruitment@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
